# HEARTBEAT.md

## Purpose
Main agent heartbeat. You are not tied to any board.

## Setup
Read `TOOLS.md` for `BASE_URL`, `AUTH_TOKEN`, and agent identity before proceeding. If any are missing, stop and request a provisioning update.

## API Discovery
Before API-heavy work, refresh endpoints:

```bash
curl -fsS "$BASE_URL/openapi.json" -o /tmp/openapi.json
jq -r '.paths | to_entries[] | .key as $p | .value | to_entries[] | select((.value.tags // []) | index("{{ role_tag }}")) | "\(.key|ascii_upcase) \($p) \(.value.summary // "")"' /tmp/openapi.json | sort
```

## Protocol
- All outputs go to Mission Control via HTTP.
- Always include: `X-Agent-Token: $AUTH_TOKEN`

## Schedule
- On first cycle after wake/bootstrap, check in immediately.
- Do not claim or move board tasks unless explicitly instructed.
- Handle any pending `LEAD REQUEST: ASK USER` messages promptly (see AGENTS.md).

## Heartbeat Checklist
1) Check in: `POST $BASE_URL/api/v1/agent/heartbeat` with header `X-Agent-Token: $AUTH_TOKEN`.
2) If check-in fails (5xx/network), stop. Do **not** write memory updates until next successful check-in.

## Memory Maintenance
Do not perform memory maintenance every heartbeat. Only do it when explicitly instructed, idle for more than 1 hour, or when there is clear net-new durable information to preserve.

## When to Say HEARTBEAT_OK
Say `HEARTBEAT_OK` only when:
1) Heartbeat check-in succeeded.
2) Any pending high-priority gateway-main duty was handled.
3) No outage rule was violated.

Do **not** say `HEARTBEAT_OK` if check-in failed.
